NAME
   ORPGDAT_PROD_INFO - product distribution adaptation data

DESCRIPTION
    This data store is a replaceable LB that contains the RPG product
    distribution adaptation data. The following messages are defined:

    Message PD_LINE_INFO_MSG_ID (1): This message stores the basic product
    distribution info including line configuration. In the message, the first
    part is a Pd_distri_info data structure. A product distribution line table
    (an array of Pd_line_entry) then follows. Note that the table must start at
    an aligned offset.

    Message PD_USER_INFO_MSG_ID (2): This message stores the user profiles. 
    This is no longer used.

    Message PD_PROD_ATTR_MSG_ID (3): This message stores general product
    information. This message is a list of entries which start with the
    Pd_attr_entry structure followed by a map (prod_id_t) list and a dependent
    product, (dep_prods_list, prod_id_t) list. Note that the each entry must
    start at an aligned offset.

    Message PD_CURRENT_PROD_MSG_ID (4): The current product generation table.
    It is a list of data structure Pd_prod_entry.

    Message PD_DEFAULT_A_PROD_MSG_ID (5): The product generation table for
    weather mode A. It is a list of data structure Pd_prod_entry.

    Message PD_DEFAULT_B_PROD_MSG_ID (6): The product generation table for
    weather mode B. It is a list of data structure Pd_prod_entry.

    Message PD_DEFAULT_M_PROD_MSG_ID (7): The product generation table for
    maintenance mode. It is a list of data structure Pd_prod_entry.

    The data structures are defined in prod_distri_info.h. ipi is a tool for
    initializing the ORPGDAT_PROD_INFO messages from information stored in
    ASCII files.

    The following liborpg library modules access ORPGDAT_PROD_INFO:
    orpgcmi, orpgnbc, orpgpat, orpgpgt, orpgprod, orpgadpt.

